Cholera - Uganda (04) 980407220736
Cholera - Uganda (05) 980428225010
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 1998
From: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
Source: New Vision, 12 Jun 1998

A new outbreak of cholera in Uganda over the past 10 days has resulted in
33 deaths out of 460 cases.
The districts most affected are Aura in the north, Kabarole in the west.
There have been eight recorded cases in Kampala, the Ugandan capital, but
no deaths reported.
Including earlier outbreaks, there have been 1,550 deaths out of 37,896
cases since Nov 1997.
